README.md
     1‚Üí# xxhash
     6‚Üíxxhash is a Go implementation of the 64-bit [xxHash] algorithm, XXH64. This is a
     7‚Üíhigh-quality hashing algorithm that is much faster than anything in the Go
     8‚Üístandard library.
     9‚Üí
    10‚ÜíThis package provides a straightforward API:
    11‚Üí
    12‚Üí```
    13‚Üífunc Sum64(b []byte) uint64
    14‚Üífunc Sum64String(s string) uint64
    15‚Üítype Digest struct{ ... }
    16‚Üí    func New() *Digest
    17‚Üí```
    18‚Üí
    19‚ÜíThe `Digest` type implements hash.Hash64. Its key methods are:
    20‚Üí
    21‚Üí```
    22‚Üífunc (*Digest) Write([]byte) (int, error)
    23‚Üífunc (*Digest) WriteString(string) (int, error)
    24‚Üífunc (*Digest) Sum64() uint64
    25‚Üí```
    26‚Üí
    27‚ÜíThe package is written with optimized pure Go and also contains even faster
    28‚Üíassembly implementations for amd64 and arm64. If desired, the `purego` build tag
    29‚Üíopts into using the Go code even on those architectures.
    30‚Üí
    31‚Üí[xxHash]: https://xxhash.com/
    32‚Üí
    33‚Üí## Compatibility
    35‚ÜíThis package is in a module and the latest code is in version 2 of the module.
    36‚ÜíYou need a version of Go with at least "minimal module compatibility" to use
    37‚Üígithub.com/cespare/xxhash/v2:
    38‚Üí
    39‚Üí* 1.9.7+ for Go 1.9
    40‚Üí* 1.10.3+ for Go 1.10
    41‚Üí* Go 1.11 or later
    42‚Üí
    43‚ÜíI recommend using the latest release of Go.
    44‚Üí
    45‚Üí## Benchmarks
    47‚ÜíHere are some quick benchmarks comparing the pure-Go and assembly
    48‚Üíimplementations of Sum64.
    49‚Üí
    50‚Üí| input size | purego    | asm       |
    51‚Üí| ---------- | --------- | --------- |
    52‚Üí| 4 B        |  1.3 GB/s |  1.2 GB/s |
    53‚Üí| 16 B       |  2.9 GB/s |  3.5 GB/s |
    54‚Üí| 100 B      |  6.9 GB/s |  8.1 GB/s |
    55‚Üí| 4 KB       | 11.7 GB/s | 16.7 GB/s |
    56‚Üí| 10 MB      | 12.0 GB/s | 17.3 GB/s |
    57‚Üí
    58‚ÜíThese numbers were generated on Ubuntu 20.04 with an Intel Xeon Platinum 8252C
    59‚ÜíCPU using the following commands under Go 1.19.2:
    60‚Üí
    61‚Üí```
    62‚Üíbenchstat <(go test -tags purego -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    63‚Üíbenchstat <(go test -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    64‚Üí```
    65‚Üí
    66‚Üí## Projects using this package
    68‚Üí- [InfluxDB](https://github.com/influxdata/influxdb)
    69‚Üí- [Prometheus](https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus)
    70‚Üí- [VictoriaMetrics](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/VictoriaMetrics)
    71‚Üí- [FreeCache](https://github.com/coocood/freecache)
    72‚Üí- [FastCache](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/fastcache)
    73‚Üí- [Ristretto](https://github.com/dgraph-io/ristretto)
    74‚Üí- [Badger](https://github.com/dgraph-io/badger)

